HEADWORD: Schemer
<hw>Schem"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who forms
schemes; a projector; esp., a plotter; an intriguer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Schemers</qex> and confederates in guilt.</q>
<rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scheming</ent>⟦br⟧
